<br>
1) Why should we care if some other guild failed a raid?<br>
2) Why is failing to kill a mob justification for sending tells full of foul language to us?<br>
3) The fact that by failing, Emperor would still be up when it cycles around to our raid time is irrelevant surely.  Indeed in this case it was especially irrelevant since we didn't go after emperor anyway. <br>
<br>
It is inexcusable to send tells full of Vitriol to people in game.  We don't send tells to your members calling you a bunch of w.ankers because we failed on a raid and left a mob up? <br>
<br>
Basically, we had absolutely no idea you had even tried emperor, the only players online from our guild were USA based players who got a screen full of abuse for no good reason.<br>
<br>
One of the players, who I will not name here was very upset by the tells received and is considering complaining to Sony about this incident. <br>
<br>
This is a plea to the leadership of TWC to reign in this particularly nasty subsection of your membership. Personal abuse is not acceptable.  In this case it was doubly unacceptable as there was no reason for it whatsoever.<br>
<br>
